"Baseline characteristics
Two hundred and sixty patients infected with HCV were enrolled in this study. Baseline characteristics of the patients are shown in Table 1. All patients were Japanese had a median age of 55.6 years, and 137 (52.7%) were male. Mean body mass index (BMI) was 23.1 kg/m2, with 45 and 9 of these patients classified as overweight (25.0–29.9 kg/m2) and obese (≥30 kg/m2), respectively. Only one patient with HCV genotype 3 was included. US revealed fatty change of the liver and hepatic cirrhosis in 127 (47.6%) and 37 (14.2%), respectively.
