No association between IL28B rs8099917 genotype and fatty change of the liver or existence of hepatic cirrhosis diagnosed by US
The patient characteristics of those with IL28B rs809917 genotype are shown in Table 3. γ-GTP levels were higher in the IL28B rs809917 minor allele (TG or GG) group than in the major allele (TT) group. However, the present study did not show any association between IL28B rs809917 genotype and fatty change of the liver or the existence of hepatic cirrhosis based on US findings.
