Comparison of patient characteristics with and without hepatic cirrhosis
The patient characteristics with and without hepatic cirrhosis according to US findings are shown in Table 6. By univariate analysis, higher BMI (P = 0.016), higher γ-GTP (P<0.01), lower platelet count (P = 0.046), lower total cholesterol (P = 0.013), higher AFP (P<0.01), higher aspartate aminotransferase/platelet ratio index (APRI) (P<0.01) and a lower proportion of fatty change of the liver (P<0.01) were observed in patients with hepatic cirrhosis. By multivariate logistic regression analysis, hepatic cirrhosis was attained independent of higher APRI, no fatty change of the liver on US findings, higher BMI and higher AFP levels (Table 7).
